September 7, 1992|accessdate=November 28, 2016}}{{Open access}}</ref> and owner Hugh Culverhouse on September 5, 1993.<ref>{{cite news|title=Kansas City vs. Tampa Bay: The Game - Headliners|url=https://www.newspapers.com/clip/7633704//|first=Robin|last=Miller|author-link=Robin Miller (journalist)|newspaper=The Orlando Sentinel|page=15|via=[[Newspapers.com]]|date=September 6, 1993|accessdate=November 28, 2016}}{{Open access}}</ref> No additional members were added before [[Tampa Stadium]] was closed and demolished; when the stadium was demolished in 1998, so was the Krewe.\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n| colspan=\"5\" style=\"{{NFLPrimaryStyle|Tampa Bay Buccaneers}};\"|'''Tampa Stadium Krewe of Honor'''\n|-\n! style=\"width:40px; {{NFLAltPrimaryStyle|Tampa Bay Buccaneers}};\"|Year\n! style=\"width:40px; {{NFLAltPrimaryStyle|Tampa Bay Buccaneers}};\"|No.\n! style=\"width:150px; {{NFLAltPrimaryStyle|Tampa Bay Buccaneers}};\"|Name\n! style=\"width:80px; {{NFLAltPrimaryStyle|Tampa Bay Buccaneers}};\"|Position\n! style=\"width:100px; {{NFLAltPrimaryStyle|Tampa Bay Buccaneers}};\"|Tenure\n|-\n|rowspan=3|1991 || 63 || [[Lee Roy Selmon]] || [[Defensive end|DE]] || 1976\u20131984 \n|-\n| \u2014 || [[John McKay (football coach)|John McKay]] || Head Coach || 1976\u20131984\n|-\n| 42 || [[Ricky Bell (running back)|Ricky Bell]] || [[Running Back|RB]] || 1977\u20131981\n|-\n| 1992 || 12 || [[Doug Williams (American football)|Doug Williams]] || [[Quarterback|QB]] || 1978\u20131982\n|-\n| 1993 || \u2014 || [[Hugh Culverhouse]] || Owner || 1976\u20131994\n|}\n\n===Ring of Honor===\nOn November 8, 2009, the team unveiled a new [[Hall of fame|Ring of Honor]] at [[Raymond James Stadium]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Edrington|first=Tom|title=Tampa Bay Buccaneers Take Selmon for Their Ring of Honor|url=http://bleacherreport.com/articles/222658-buccaneers-take-selmon-for-their-ring-of-honor|website=Bleacher Report|date=July 23, 2009|accessdate=September 18, 2016}}</ref>\n[[File:RaymondJamesStadiumRingofHonor.JPG|thumb|300px|The Ring of Honor at Raymond James Stadium]]\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n|style=\"background:#ffb\"|Elected to the [[Pro Football Hall of Fame]]\n|}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n| colspan=\"5\" style=\"{{NFLPrimaryStyle|Tampa Bay Buccaneers}};\"|'''Tampa Bay Buccaneers Ring of Honor'''\n|-\n! style=\"width:40px; {{NFLAltPrimaryStyle|Tampa Bay Buccaneers}};\"|Year\n! style=\"width:40px; {{NFLAltPrimaryStyle|Tampa Bay Buccaneers}};\"|No.\n! style=\"width:150px; {{NFLAltPrimaryStyle|Tampa Bay Buccaneers}};\"|Name\n! style=\"width:80px; {{NFLAltPrimaryStyle|Tampa Bay Buccaneers}};\"|Position\n! style=\"width:80px; {{NFLAltPrimaryStyle|Tampa Bay Buccaneers}};\"|Tenure\n|-\n| 2009 || 63 || style=\"background:#ffb\"|[[Lee Roy Selmon]] || [[Defensive end|DE]] || 1976\u20131984 \n|-\n| 2010 || \u2014 || [[John McKay (American football)|John McKay]] || Head Coach || 1976\u20131984\n|-\n| 2011 || 88 || [[Jimmie Giles]] || [[Tight End|TE]] || 1978\u20131986\n|-\n| 2012 || 74 || [[Paul Gruber]] || [[Offensive Tackle|OT]] || 1988\u20131999\n|-\n| 2013 || 99 || style=\"background:#ffb\"|[[Warren Sapp]] || [[Defensive Tackle|DT]] || 1995\u20132003\n|-\n| 2014 || 55 || style=\"background:#ffb\"|[[Derrick Brooks]] || [[Linebacker|LB]] || 1995\u20132008\n|-\n|rowspan=2|2015 || 40 || [[Mike Alstott]] || [[Fullback (gridiron football)|FB]]  || 1996\u20132007\n|-\n| 12 || [[Doug Williams (American football)|Doug Williams]] || [[Quarterback|QB]] || 1978\u20131982\n|-\n| 2016 || 47 || [[John Lynch (American football)|John Lynch]] || [[Safety (gridiron football position)|S]] || 1993\u20132003\n|-\n|rowspan=2| 2017 || \u2014 || [[Malcolm Glazer]] || Owner || 1995\u20132014\n|-\n| \u2014 || [[Jon Gruden]] || Head Coach || 2002\u20132008\n|-\n| 2018 || \u2014 || style=\"background:#ffb\"|[[Tony Dungy]] || Head Coach || 1996\u20132001\n|-\n| 2019 || 20 || [[Ronde Barber]] || [[Defensive Back|DB]] || 1997\u20132012\n|}\n\n===Pro Bowl selections===\nMany former and current Tampa Bay Buccaneers players have represented the franchise in the [[Pro Bowl]]:\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n| colspan=\"5\" style=\"{{NFLPrimaryStyle|Tampa Bay Buccaneers}};\"|'''Tampa Bay Buccaneers Pro Bowl selections'''\n|-\n! style=\"width:40px; {{NFLAltPrimaryStyle|Tampa Bay Buccaneers}};\"|No. of Pro Bowls\n! style=\"width:150px; {{NFLAltPrimaryStyle|Tampa Bay Buccaneers}};\"|Player\n! style=\"width:40px; {{NFLAltPrimaryStyle|Tampa Bay Buccaneers}};\"|Position\n! style=\"width:100px; {{NFLAltPrimaryStyle|Tampa Bay Buccaneers}};\"|Tenure\n! style=\"width:100px; {{NFLAltPrimaryStyle|Tampa Bay Buccaneers}};\"|Pro Bowls\n|-\n|11 ||[[Derrick Brooks]]||LB||1995\u20132008||[[1997 Pro Bowl|1997]], [[1998 Pro Bowl|1998]], [[1999 Pro Bowl|1999]], [[2000 Pro Bowl|2000]], [[2001 Pro Bowl|2001]], [[2002 Pro Bowl|2002]], [[2003 Pro Bowl|2003]], [[2004 Pro Bowl|2004]], [[2005 Pro Bowl|2005]], [[2006 Pro Bowl|2006]], [[2008 Pro Bowl|2008]]\n|-\n|7 ||[[Warren Sapp]]||DT||1995\u20132003||[[1997 Pro Bowl|1997]], [[1998 Pro Bowl|1998]], [[1999 Pro Bowl|1999]], [[2000 Pro Bowl|2000]], [[2001 Pro Bowl|2001]], [[2002 Pro Bowl|2002]], [[2003 Pro Bowl|2003]]\n|-\n|6||[[Lee Roy Selmon]]||DE||1976\u20131984||[[1979 Pro Bowl|1979]], [[1980 Pro Bowl|1980]], [[1981 Pro Bowl|1981]], [[1982 Pro Bowl|1982]], [[1983 Pro Bowl|1983]], [[1984 Pro Bowl|1984]]\n|-\n|6||[[Mike Alstott]]||FB||1996\u20132007||[[1997 Pro Bowl|1997]], [[1998 Pro Bowl|1998]], [[1999 Pro Bowl|1999]], [[2000 Pro Bowl|2000]], [[2001 Pro Bowl|2001]], [[2002 Pro Bowl|2002]]\n|-\n|6||[[Gerald McCoy]]||DT||2010\u20132018||[[2013 Pro Bowl|2012]], [[2014 Pro Bowl|2013]], [[2015 Pro Bowl|2014]], [[2016 Pro Bowl|2015]], [[2017 Pro Bowl|2016]], [[2018 Pro Bowl|2017]]\n|-\n|5||[[Hardy Nickerson]]||LB||1993\u20131999||[[1993 Pro Bowl|1993]], [[1996 Pro Bowl|1996]], [[1997 Pro Bowl|1997]], [[1998 Pro Bowl|1998]], [[19