oles. The film had musical score by Br. Lakshmanan.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.malayalachalachithram.com/movie.php?i=97|title=Sreeraama Pattaabhishekam|accessdate=2014-10-10|publisher=www.malayalachalachithram.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://malayalasangeetham.info/m.php?1781|title=Sreeraama Pattaabhishekam|accessdate=2014-10-10|publisher=malayalasangeetham.info}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://spicyonion.com/title/shree-rama-pattabhishekam-malayalam-movie/|title=Sreeraama Pattaabhishekam|accessdate=2014-10-10|publisher=spicyonion.com}}</ref>\n\n==Cast==\n*[[Prem Nazir]] as [[Rama|Sree Raman]]\n*[[Vasanthi (actress)|Vasanthi]] as Seetha/Ahalya\n*[[Kaviyoor Ponnamma]]  as [[Mandodari]]\n*[[Thikkurissi Sukumaran Nair]] as [[Dasaratha|Dasaradhan]]\n*[[Prem Nawas]] as [[Lakshmana]]n\n*[[G. K. Pillai (actor)|GK Pillai]] as [[Vishwamitra|Vishwamithran]]\n*[[Miss Kumari]] as [[Kaikeyi]]\n*[[K. V. Shanthi]] as [[Surpanakha]]/Kamavalli\n*[[T. K. Balachandran]] as [[Bharata (Ramayana)|Bharathan]]\n*[[Aranmula Ponnamma]] as [[Kausalya]]\n*[[Jose Prakash]] as [[Janaka]]raja\n*[[Kaduvakulam Antony]] as Badan\n*[[Kottarakkara Sreedharan Nair]] as [[Ravana]]n\n*[[Vanchiyoor Radha]] as Mallika\n*[[Adoor Pankajam]] as [[Manthara]]\n*[[Hari (actor)|Hari]] as [[Shatrughna]]n\n*[[S. P. Pillai]] as Vaidyar\n*[[Sukumari]] dance appearance in song sequence\n\n==Soundtrack==\nThe music was composed by Br. Lakshmanan and lyrics were written by Thirunayinaarkurichi Madhavan Nair. Slokas taken from [[Thunchathu Ezhuthachan]]'s [[Adhyathmaramayanam]] were also taken to the film.\n{| border=\"2\" cellpadding=\"4\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin: 1em 1em 1em 0; background: #f9f9f9; border: 1px #aaa solid; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 95%;\" \n|- bgcolor=\"#CCCCCF\" align=\"center\" \n| '''No.''' || '''Song''' || '''Singers''' ||'''Lyrics''' || '''Length (m:ss)''' \n|- \n| 1 || \"Chollu Sakhi\" || [[P. Susheela]] || Thirunayinaarkurichi Madhavan Nair || \n|- \n| 2 || \"Lankesha\" || [[P. Leela]], [[Soolamangalam Rajalakshmi]] || Thirunayinaarkurichi Madhavan Nair || \n|- \n| 3 || \"Mama Tharuni\" || [[Kamukara]] || Thirunayinaarkurichi Madhavan Nair || \n|- \n| 4 || \"Mohini Njaan\" || [[S. Janaki]] || Thirunayinaarkurichi Madhavan Nair || \n|- \n| 5 || \"Naaduvaazhuvaan\" || [[K. J. Yesudas]], P. Susheela, [[Kamukara]], [[A. P. Komala]], Chorus || Thirunayinaarkurichi Madhavan Nair || \n|- \n| 6 || \"Ninne Piriyukil\" || [[P. B. Sreenivas]] || Thirunayinaarkurichi Madhavan Nair || \n|- \n| 7 || \"Parannu Parannu\" || P. Susheela, Kamukara || Thirunayinaarkurichi Madhavan Nair || \n|- \n| 8 || \"Pokunnitha\" || [[P. B. Sreenivas]], Chorus || Thirunayinaarkurichi Madhavan Nair || \n|- \n| 9 || \"Ponnittu Porulittu\" || P. Susheela, Kamukara || Thirunayinaarkurichi Madhavan Nair, Thunchathezhuthachan || \n|- \n| 10 || \"Pookkaatha Kaadukale\" (Theyyare) || K. J. Yesudas, Chorus || Thirunayinaarkurichi Madhavan Nair || \n|- \n| 11 || \"Raajaadhi Raaja\" || [[A. P. Komala]], [[Jikki]], Vaidehi || Thirunayinaarkurichi Madhavan Nair || \n|- \n| 12 || \"Raamaraama Seetha\" || K. J. Yesudas, Chorus || Thirunayinaarkurichi Madhavan Nair || \n|- \n| 13 || \"Sooryavamshathin\" || P. Leela, Kamukara || Thirunayinaarkurichi Madhavan Nair || \n|- \n| 14 || \"Thaathan Nee Mathavu\" || P. B. Sreenivas || Thirunayinaarkurichi Madhavan Nair || \n|- \n| 15 || \"Vatsa Soumithre\" || Kamukara || Thunchathezhuthachan || \n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|0253690|Shree Rama Pattabhishekam}}\n\n[[Category:1962 films]]\n[[Category:Indian films]]\n[[Category:1960s Malayalam-language films]]\n[[Category:Films based on the Ramayana]] \n\n{1960s-Malayalam-film-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Titodutta", "label": "safe", "comment": "linkP. SubramaniamusingFind link.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sreerama_Pattabhishekam"}
{"title_page": "Don Fernando", "text_new": "{{Multiple issues|\n{{BLP sources|date=October 2007}}\n{{COI|date=April 2020}}\n}}\n{{Infobox adult biography\n| name            = Don Fernando\n| image           = [[File:2006 Don Fernando 01.jpg|180px]]\n| caption         = Fernando in 2006\n| birth_name      = \n| birth_date      = {{birth date and age|1948|04|12}}\n| birth_place     = [[San Francisco]], [[California]], U.S.\n| death_date      = \n| death_place     = \n| spouse          = \n| height          = {{height|ft=5|in=8}}\n| weight          = {{convert|160|lb|kg st|abbr=on}}\n| alias           = Asianman, Mr. Camera\n| number_of_films = 1502 as a performer & 133 as a director (per [[IAFD]])<ref name=IAFD>{{iafd name|DFernando|M|Don Fernando}}. Retrieved on 2012-11-01.</ref>\n| website         = \n}}\n\n'''Don Fernando''' (born April 12, 1948) is a [[Film director|director]] and [[pornographic actor|actor]] of [[pornographic film]]s. He started  in the pornography business in 1977 and performed for 39 consecutive years; the longest tenure for any male pornographic film actor in the world, until his retirement in 2016. He won the Best Supporting Actor Award twice (1995{{Citation needed|date=October 2007}} and in 2005) during the [[Barcelona International Erotic Film Festival|Festival de Cine Erotica-Barcelona]]<ref>{{cite press release|title=LISTADO DE PEL\u00cdCULAS PREMIADAS |publisher=[[FICEB]] |date=October 2005 |url=http://www.ficeb.com/notas_prensa/Listado%20premiados.pdf |format=PDF, Spanish/English |accessdate=2007-10-07 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070927034414/http://www.ficeb.com/notas_prensa/Listado%20premiados.pdf |archivedate=September 27, 2007 }}</ref> Fernando was inducted into the [[XRCO Hall of Fame|X-Rated Critics Organization Hall of Fame]] in 1997.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bwdl.net/XRCO-2/hall.htm |title=XRCO Hall of Fame |accessdate=2007-10-07 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071007005528/http://www.bwdl.net/XRCO-2/hall.htm |archivedate=2007-10-07 }}</ref> He was inducted into the ''[[AVN (magazine)|AVN]]'' [[AVN Hall of Fame|Hall of Fame]] during the 2004 [[AVN Awards]].<ref>{{cite news|title=AVN Awards Winners|work=[[AVN (magazine)|Adult Video News]]|url=http://www.avn.com/index.cfm?objectID=ED9E585D-1372-4B41-C4A4DA6742B42BDF&slid=114684|date=2004-01-10|accessdate=2007-10-07|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071111005451/http://www.avn.com/index.cfm?objectID=ED9E585D-1372-4B41-C4A4DA6742B42BDF&slid=114684|archivedate=2007-11-11}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{iafd name|DFernando|M|Don Fernando}}\n* {{afdb name|id=585|gender=male|name=Don Fernando}}\n* {{IMDb name|0273077}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Fernando, Don}}\n[[Category:1948 births]]\n[[Category:American male pornographic film actors]]\n[[Category:American pornographic film directors]]\n[[Category:Hispanic and Latino American pornographic film actors]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n\n\n{{Porn-actor-stub}}\n{{US-film-director-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Multiple issues|\n{{BLP sources|date=October 2007}}\n{{COI|date=April 2020}}\n}}\n{{Infobox adult biography\n| name            = Don Fernando\n| image           = [[File:2006 Don Fernando 01.jpg|180px]]\n| caption         = Fernando in 2006\n| birth_name      = \n| birth_date      = {{birth date and age|1948|04|12}}\n| birth_place     = [[San Francisco]], [[California]], U.S.\n| death_date      = \n| death_place     = \n| spouse          = \n| height          = {{height|ft=5|in=8}}\n| weight          = {{convert|160|lb|kg st|abbr=on}}\n| alias           = Asianman, Mr. Camera\n| number_of_films = 1502 as a performer & 133 as a director (per [[IAFD]])<ref name=IAFD>{{iafd name|DFernando|M|Don Fernando}}. Retrieved on 2012-11-01.</ref>\n| website         = \n}}\n\n'''Don Fernando''' (born April 12, 1948) is a [[Film director|director]] and [[pornographic actor|actor]] of [[pornographic film]]s. He started  in the pornography business in 1977 and performed for 39 consecutive years; the longest tenure for any male pornographic film actor in the world, until his retirement in 2016. He won the Best Supporting Actor Award twice (1995{{Citation needed|date=October 2007}} and in 2005) during the [[Barcelona International Erotic Film Festival|Festival de Cine Erotica-Barcelona]]<ref>{{cite press release|title=LISTADO DE PEL\u00cdCULAS PREMIADAS |publisher=[[FICEB]] |date=October 2005 |url=http://www.ficeb.com/notas_prensa/Listado%20premiados.pdf |format=PDF, Spanish/English |accessdate=2007-10-07 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070927034414/http://www.ficeb.com/notas_prensa/Listado%20premiados.pdf |archivedate=September 27, 2007 }}</ref> Fernando was inducted into the [[XRCO Hall of Fame|X-Rated Critics Organization Hall of Fame]] in 1997.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bwdl.net/XRCO-2/hall.htm |title=XRCO Hall of Fame |accessdate=2007-10-07 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071007005528/http://www.bwdl.net/XRCO-2/hall.htm |archivedate=2007-10-07 }}</ref> He was inducted into the ''[[AVN (magazine)|AVN]]'' [[AVN Hall of Fame|Hall of Fame]] during the 2004 [[AVN Awards]].<ref>{{cite news|title=AVN Awards Winners|work=[[AVN (magazine)|Adult Video News]]|url=http://www.avn.com/index.cfm?objectID=ED9E585D-1372-4B41-C4A4DA6742B42BDF&slid=114684|date=2004-01-10|accessdate=2007-10-07|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071111005451/http://www.avn.com/index.cfm?objectID=ED9E585D-1372-4B41-C4A4DA6742B42BDF&slid=114684|archivedate=2007-11-11}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{iafd name|DFernando|M|Don Fernando}}\n* {{afdb name|id=585|gender=male|name=Don Fernando}}\n* {{IMDb name|0273077}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Fernando, Don}}\n[[Category:1948 births]]\n[[Category:American male pornographic film actors]]\n[[Category:American pornographic film directors]]\n[[Category:Hispanic and Latino American pornographic film actors]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n", "name_user": "Ionmars10", "label": "safe", "comment": "+{{Porn-actor-stub}}, +{{US-film-director-stub}} usingStubSorter", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Don_Fernando"}
